<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <% include ../../partials/header.ejs %>
  <script src="/scripts/java-playground.js"></script>
  <script src='https://www.google.com/recaptcha/api.js'></script>
</head>

<body>

<% include ../../partials/header-playground-java.ejs %>
<% include ../../partials/header-playground-java-steps.ejs %>
    
<!-- Tutorial steps -->
<div class="container">

  <p class="mt-3">Let's create an advanced Java app in the <strong>Marketing Cloud SDK Playground</strong>. This app will connect to Marketing Cloud, send an e-mail to a contact you specify and check status of the e-mail.</p>

  <p class="mt-3">Like before, this Java app uses pre-provisioned API Keys (<code>Client ID</code> and <code>Client Secret</code>) from the <strong>Marketing Cloud SDK Playground</strong> environment to connect to Marketing Cloud.</p>
  
  <div class="card mt-3">
    <div class="card-block">
      <div class="card-header text-white" style="background-color: #00AA9E;">Send a test e-mail with Marketing Cloud</div>
      <div class="card-body">
        <h6 class="card-subtitle mb-3">Complete the following steps to run the Java app in the playground.</h6>
        
        <form id="frmRunApp2" action="/playgound-api/java/runapp2" method="post">
          <div class="form-group">
            <p class="card-text"><mark>Step 1:</mark> Prove you're a human. We do this to protect this website against spam and abuse.</p>
            <div class="g-recaptcha m-3" data-sitekey="6Levl0UUAAAAAJFcKN0fYZBoulC2mmJslaCFyNlD"></div>
          </div>

          <div class="form-group">
            <label for="inputEmail"><mark>Step 2:</mark> Enter the receipient's e-mail address.</label>
            <input required type="email" class="form-control" name="inputEmail" id="inputEmail" aria-describedby="emailHelp" placeholder="Recepient's email address (required)">
            <small id="emailHelp" class="form-text text-muted">This e-mail address is only used for testing purposes and never shared with anyone. See <a href="https://trust.salesforce.com" target="_blank">https://trust.salesforce.com</a></small>
          </div>

          <div class="form-group">
            <p class="card-text"><mark>Step 3:</mark> Click <strong>Compile and Run Java app</strong> to run the app in the playground.</p>
            <p class="card-text">Running the Java app will cause Marketing Cloud to send a <strong>test</strong> e-mail to the receipient you specified above.</p>
            <p class="card-text">Lines <code>10 and 11</code> in the code below use the <code>Client ID</code> and <code>Client Secret</code> from the <strong>Marketing Cloud SDK Playground</strong> environment. Line <code>12</code> is updated with your receipient's e-mail address.</p>
            <button id="buttonRunApp2" class="btn btn-secondary" type="submit">Compile and Run Java app</button>
          </div>
        </form>
          
        <pre id="playground-java-app2" style="max-height: 30em" class="line-numbers" data-line="10-11" data-src="/code-snippets/java/app2-playground.java"></pre>

        <div class="card mt-3">
          <div class="card-header"><small>CONSOLE OUTPUT</small></div>
          <pre style="max-height: 30em" class="m-2">
            <code id="outputRunApp" class="language-bash">Nothing yet. Complete the steps above to see results.</code>
          </pre>
        </div>

        <div id="successRunApp" class="hide-element">
          <p class="card-text mt-3"><span class="fa fa-star text-success"></span>&nbsp;Congrats. You have sucessfully compiled and run an advanced Java app in the <strong>Marketing Cloud Playground!</strong></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>

<% include ../../partials/footer.ejs %>

</body>
</html>